<p>
<seg id=1> Francisco Aguirre-Sacasa, Nicaragua's ambassador to the United States, appealed to creditor nations to annul the debts of Central American nations and to provide reconstruction aid to these countries in order to help them recover from the damage inflicted by Hurricane Mitch. </seg>
<seg id=2> Sacasa said on American television that reconstruction of Nicaragua will require approximately one billion U.S. dollars. He urged the United States and other creditor nations to draw up a complete set of proposals similar to the postwar economic aid of the Marshall Plan given to Western Europe. </seg>
